<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Treacherous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Treacherous,</orth> committing treason, faithless, perfidious: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 4, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.54.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.211" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 171</bibl> (not in Ff). <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.609" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 609</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.327" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 327</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.317" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 317</bibl>. <cit><quote>sheep run not half so t. from the wolf . . . as you fly from your oft-subdued slaves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 30</bibl></cit>. (some M. Edd. <emph>timorous.</emph> But in the opinion and language of a man like Talbot cowardice is treachery; cf. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 35</bibl>, and see <emph>trusty</emph> in <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 23</bibl>). cf. also <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 83</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>